    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12748#discussion_r2912356768\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>While I <a href=\"https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&amp;mode=debug&amp;edition=2024&amp;gist=a979495cee5560168ab3795d72c930fc\">thought it was possible</a> to return <code>&amp;mut ZST</code>, apparently that's only implemented for empty arrays in rustc rather than all empty types -- hence the array here. It was the only way I could think of to safely get a <code>&amp;'static mut T</code> to implement the trait on.</p>\n</blockquote>",
